## ğŸ” Chapter 3: How LLMs Work â€“ Internals & Intuition

At the heart of every modern LLM lies the **Transformer**. Hereâ€™s how it thinks:

### ğŸ§  The Transformer Workflow
1. **Tokenization**  
   Text â†’ subword tokens â†’ numerical IDs  
   *Example*: `"Generative AI is fun!"` â†’ `["Gener", "ative", " AI", " is", " fun", "!"]`

2. **Embedding**  
   Each token â†’ dense vector (e.g., 4096 numbers) encoding semantic meaning.

3. **Self-Attention**  
   The model asks: *â€œWhich words matter most when understanding this word?â€*  
   Mathematically:
   $$
   \text{Attention}(Q, K, V) = \text{softmax}\left(\frac{QK^T}{\sqrt{d_k}}\right)V
   $$

4. **Inference**  
   Predict next token â†’ repeat â†’ generate full response.

> ğŸ”¬ **Real-World Analogy**:  
> An LLM is like a **brilliant intern** whoâ€™s read the entire internetâ€”but knows nothing about your company.  
> Your job? Give them your **HR handbook** (context) and **clear instructions** (prompts)â€”and they become a star employee.

